<item>
            <title>[SEC-211] AnonymousProcessingFilter causes IllegalStateException after HttpSession invalidation (ie logout)</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-211</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=22987&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=22987&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After a HttpSession is invalidated, which is generally a result of a logout operation, the try..catch..finally block within AuthenticationProcessingFilter is causing an IllegalStateException with text &quot;Cannot create a session after the response has been committed&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This bug appeared only in 1.0.0 RC2 (version 1.10 of AuthenticationProcessingFilter). It did not appear in 1.0.0 RC1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was fixed in CVS version 1.11 of the code, which was NOT part of 1.0.0 RC2. It was fixed as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-183&quot; title=&quot;Avoid unnecessary HttpSession creation when using Anonymous and Remember-Me authentication&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-183&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-183&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (which is unrelated to this bug).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
